  "all_platforms_descr": null,
  "non_oss_deps": null,
  "anticipated_spec_changes": null,
  "security_risks": null,
  "ergonomics_risks": null,
  "wpt": null,
  "wpt_descr": "Proposal here, filed some months ago: https://github.com/web-platform-tests/rfcs/pull/233 \n\nStill in review, but feedback is generally positive. It's about a\n`<meta name=\"safe-printable-inset\" content=\"[inset-specifier]\">` to be specified in WPT print tests.\n\n`inset-specifier` is a numeric value in centimeters, which is the largest unprintable inset among the four edges of the paper sheet.\n\nThis is already implemented in Chromium's content_shell WPT testrunner, and a few tentative tests have been upstreamed. All pagination tests are handled by this testrunner in Chromium, since the headless Chrome testrunner doesn't handle pagination reliably.",
